text.section:
A licensed agent may solicit for and issue personal travel accident insurance policies by means of mechanical vending machines supervised by the agent and placed at airports and similar places of convenience to the traveling public, if the commissioner finds that:
The policy provides reasonable coverage and benefits, is suitable for sale and issuance by vending machine, and that use of such a machine in a proposed location would be of material convenience to the public;
The type of machine proposed to be used is reasonably suitable for the purpose;
Reasonable means are provided for informing prospective purchasers of policy coverages and restrictions;
Reasonable means are provided for the refund of money inserted in defective machines and for which insurance so paid for is not received; and
The cost of maintaining such a machine at a particular location is reasonable in amount.
